 HTML Image Maps

 The HTML <map> tag defines an image map.
  An image map is an image with clickable areas. 
 The areas are defined with one or more <area> tags.
 The idea behind an image map is that you should be able to perform different actions depending on where in the image you click.
 he only difference from other images is that you must add a usemap attribute

 <img src="workplace.jpg" alt="Workplace" usemap="#workmap">
 Then, add a <map> element.
The <map> element is used to create an image map, and is linked to the image by using the required name attribute
<map name="workmap">
The area of the click in the image can be 
rectangle - need coordinate of the diagonal
circle - need coordinat eof the centre and radius
poly - need coordinate of the every corner.

<area shape= "rect" coords="34, 44, 270,350" href="link">

HTML Background Images
To add a background image on an HTML element, use the HTML style attribute and the CSS background-image property
<p style="background-image: url('img_girl.jpg');">

but if want to show background image for hte page have to give  in the body element tag
body {
  background-image: url('img_girl.jpg');
}

If the background image is smaller than the element, the image will repeat itself, horizontally and vertically, until it reaches the end of the element
So, To avoid the background image from repeating itself, set the background-repeat property
to no-repeat
Can also set background-size to cover to the cover the whole element.
Can   set  background-size: 100% 100%; to strech the image
  background-attachment: fixed; this property is used to make the image fixed and entire element is always covered.


HTML <picture> Element
The HTML <picture> element allows you to display different pictures for different devices or screen sizes.
The <picture> element contains one or more <source> elements, each referring to different images through the srcset attribute.
 This way the browser can choose the image that best fit the current view and/or device.
Each <source> element has a media attribute that defines when the image is the most suitable and in that will have to define the dimension whiich suits that image the most.
<picture>
  <source media="(min-width: 650px)" srcset="img_food.jpg">
  <source media="(min-width: 465px)" srcset="img_car.jpg">
  <img src="img_girl.jpg">
</picture>

This element is used for 2 main reasons
1. to save the bandwidth and to laosd the most appropriate image nned according to device as small device would need only small image.
and 2. would be the format support if one donot support some format it would give diffrent image format to show.


HTML Favicon - A favicon is a small image displayed next to the page title in the browser tab. it is the .ico file .

it is declared in the head element tag of the 
<link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/images/favicon.ico">


