HTML Iframes
An HTML iframe is used to display a web page within a web page.
The HTML <iframe> tag specifies an inline frame.
Syntax
<iframe src="url" title="description"></iframe>
Have to use the height and width attributes to specify the size of the iframe or can use them in the style asstubute property and use its border property to speacify border or none. 
Iframe - Target for a Link can open a form in the iframe using the link to open wihtout refresing whole page
An iframe can be used as the target frame for a link.
The target attribute of the link must refer to the name attribute of the iframe.

HTML Javascript.
JavaScript makes HTML pages more dynamic and interactive.
The HTML <script> tag is used to define a client-side scrip (JavaScript).
To select an HTML element, JavaScript most often uses the document.getElementById() method
The HTML <noscript> tag defines an alternate content to be displayed to users that have disabled scripts in their browser or have a browser that doesn't support scripts



HTML File Paths
A file path describes the location of a file in a web site's folder structure.
An absolute file path is the full URL to a file:
A relative file path points to a file relative to the current page or root folder.
'/' is used to show that link is located at the root of the current web
'../" is used to show folder one level up from the current folder
It is best practice to use relative file paths (if possible).

